â­ Interview-Friendly Answer (Short)
git reset rewrites history by moving HEAD to an earlier commit and discarding subsequent commits. It is unsafe for shared branches.
git revert creates a new commit that undoes a previous commit without modifying history. It is safe for public/shared repositories.